org.sbml.jsbml.xml
Class XMLAttributes

java.lang.Object
  org.sbml.jsbml.xml.XMLAttributes

public class XMLAttributes
extends Object

Representation of the attributes on an XML node.

This class of objects is defined by jsbml only and has no direct equivalent in terms of SBML components. This class is not prescribed by the SBML specifications, although it is used to implement features defined in SBML.

Since:
0.8
Version:
$Rev: 1121 $

Adds an attribute (a name/value pair) to this XMLAttributes set optionally with a prefix and URI defining a namespace.

Parameters:
name - a string, the local name of the attribute.
value - a string, the value of the attribute.
namespaceURI - a string, the namespace URI of the attribute.
prefix - a string, the prefix of the namespace

Returns:
integer value indicating success/failure of the function. The possible values returned by this function are:
  • OPERATION_SUCCESS

    Note
    if local name with the same namespace URI already exists in this attribute set, its value and prefix will be replaced.

    • getIndex

    public int getIndex(String name)
    Returns the index of an attribute with the given name.

    Parameters:
    name - a string, the local name of the attribute for which the index is required.

    Returns:
    the index of an attribute with the given local name, or -1 if not present.
    Note
    A namespace bound to the name is not checked by this function. Thus, if there are multiple attributes with the given local name and different namespaces, the smallest index among those attributes will be returned. getIndex(String name, String uri) or getIndex(XMLTriple triple) should be used to get an index of an attribute with the given local name and namespace.

    getValue

    public String getValue(String name)
    Returns an attribute's value by name.

    Parameters:
    name - a string, the local name of the attribute whose value is required.

    Returns:
    The attribute value as a string.

    Note
    If an attribute with the given local name does not exist, an empty string will be returned. Use hasAttribute(String name, String uri) to test for attribute existence. A namespace bound to the local name is not checked by this function. Thus, if there are multiple attributes with the given local name and different namespaces, the value of an attribute with the smallest index among those attributes will be returned. getValue(String name) or getValue(XMLTriple triple) should be used to get a value of an attribute with the given local name and namespace.
